{
  "name": "Suppressing Fire",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "modules/pf1spheres/assets/icons/spheres/barrage.webp",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>When performing a barrage, you may make 2 extra attacks instead of one, but must target the same creature with both of these extra attacks. However, your shots are wild, and the target can easily duck, causing both of your extra attacks to miss. However, doing so causes the target to have its movement speed reduced by half and to suffer a -3 penalty to Perception checks and to all attack rolls until the end of their next round, -1 for each additional extra attack augmented with the suppressing fire (blitz) that targets this creature. The target can choose not to avoid these attacks, in which case you may roll the attacks as normal, and the target doesn&#8217;t suffer the penalties.</p>\n",
